output: For each test case, print how many digits have the multiple of n that attends the above requisites.
input: The input consists in many test cases and ends with EOF. Each test case contains one integer n (1 ≤ n ≤ 10000) not divisible by 2 or 5.
name: Ones
description:
Given any integer n (1 ≤ n ≤ 10000) not divisible by 2 
                    or 5, some multiple of n is a number which in decimal notation is a sequence of 
                    1\'s. How many digits are in the smallest such a multiple of n?
